%% Diagram: Request coalescing (single-flight) collapses concurrent misses to one DB query
%% Type: sequence
sequenceDiagram
    participant C1 as Caller 1
    participant C2 as Caller 2
    participant CN as Caller N
    participant SF as Single-flight group
    participant Cache
    participant DB

    C1->>Cache: GET key
    Cache-->>C1: miss
    C1->>SF: Do(key, fetch)
    Note over SF: Records key as in-flight; first caller becomes the leader

    C2->>Cache: GET key
    Cache-->>C2: miss
    C2->>SF: Do(key, fetch)
    Note right of SF: Caller 2 attaches to the existing leader; no DB call issued

    CN->>SF: Do(key, fetch)
    Note right of SF: Caller N attaches; still one in-flight request

    SF->>DB: SELECT key
    DB-->>SF: value
    SF->>Cache: SET key value
    SF-->>C1: value
    SF-->>C2: value
    SF-->>CN: value
    Note over SF: 10K concurrent missers, 1 DB query, 9999 waiters share the result
